Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!

Regards, 
PharmEasy

notes.body: Hello Rohit,   Greetings from PharmEasy!  With reference to your personal data deletion request, I am sorry to inform you that we are unable to delete the account from our database. As we have to show all transactions or interactions, past or present when asked for by relevant Government authorities.    However, kindly confirm with us if you wish to deactivate the account or want to stop receiving promotional SMS/Emails so that we can check and do the needful at the earliest.  Let me inform you that, once the account is deactivated then we cannot process any request or reactivate the account. Once confirmed our team will reach out to complete the account deactivation process on a registered mobile number to confirm if you requested account deactivation. If yes, OTP will be generated and will be sent to your registered mobile number. Once the OTP is shared by you to the team then will go ahead and block your account.   Awaiting your response.         Regards,  Devdas.

Awaiting your response.

notes.body: Hello Nagendra,      Greetings from PharmEasy!     With regard to promotional SMS, we always try to keep our customers updated on our offers. However, we apologize for the inconvenience caused due to our promotional messages.     Please be assured, I have forwarded your request to unsubscribe your number 9705333620 from receiving promotional SMS. It will take 3 working days to process it completely. You will only receive your order-related information. Also, if you have a dual SIM phone, I would request you to help us with the second number as well. We will forward a request for the other number as well.      Further, if you wish to unsubscribe from getting the promotional notifications on your email ID too, I request you to open your latest promotional email and hit unsubscribe at the bottom right-hand side corner to stop email promotions.     I certainly hope this helps and appreciate your understanding and patience in the meanwhile.      Awaiting your response.     Regards,  Sandhya Nackwal

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear PharmEasy Support Team,

I am writing this email to formally lodge a complaint regarding the
unacceptable service I experienced with a lab test booking for my uncle
through PharmEasy.

The blood sample was collected today Dec5th 2025, I had a doctor’s
appointment scheduled at 10:00 PM IST, and your team repeatedly assured me
that the report would be delivered on time. However, when I checked the
status later, the test was shown as “Rejected” with the vague reasons of
“technical failure” and “quality check failed.”

This is extremely distressing and irresponsible, especially considering
that my uncle is weak and unwell, and now you are asking for another blood
sample due to your internal failure. This is not just an inconvenience—it
is mental and physical harassment of a patient and family.

There was:

No proactive communication from your side

No accountability for the failure

No consideration for the patient’s condition

No assurance of urgent resolution

Such negligence from a healthcare service provider is completely
unacceptable. I trusted PharmEasy with a critical medical test, and this
breach of trust has caused emotional distress and potential risk to the
patient’s health.

I demand the following:

1. Immediate written explanation for the test rejection.


2. Full refund of the test amount ( not fot just rejected tests)

3. Compensation for inconvenience and mental harassment.


4. Confirmation that strict action is taken to avoid such incidents in
future.



If I do not receive a proper resolution within 24 hours, I will be forced
to escalate this matter to:

Consumer Helpline (Government of India)

National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission (NCDRC)

Social media and public platforms


Kindly treat this matter as URGENT.

Regards,
Ajaz Ahmed
+918374416616
Hyderabad, India
